<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-250] Makefault mediator does not handle POX or REST properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-250</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Below are the scenarios which were tried out&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Scenario 1 - Sending a POX request&lt;br/&gt;
======================&lt;br/&gt;
1. Created a configuration as follows&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;sequence name=&quot;xslt_transfom_sequence&quot; onError=&quot;fault&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;in&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;xslt key=&quot;xslt_for_request&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                    &amp;lt;address uri=&quot;http://[host]:[port]/services/[service_name]&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;/endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/in&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;out&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;send/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/out&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/sequence&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;sequence name=&quot;fault&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;log/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;makefault version=&quot;soap12&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;code xmlns:sf12=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2003/05/soap-envelope&quot; value=&quot;sf12:Receiver&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;reason value=&quot;Exception occurred when transforming the request/response&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/makefault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;header name=&quot;To&quot; action=&quot;remove&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;property name=&quot;RESPONSE&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/sequence&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. The XSLT file that this configuration is accessing is an invalid XSLT.&lt;br/&gt;
3. Send a POX request through the client and expect a POX fault but actually it sends a SOAP fault&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Scenario 2 - Sending a REST request&lt;br/&gt;
=======================&lt;br/&gt;
Using the same configuration given above, send a REST request. It sends a SOAP fault and not a fault in REST&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
