                            <comment id="12577847" author="ruwan" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 13:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just checked the behavior of Synapse on faults for POX messages, and found that what we send as the fault is somewhat like following, which is not wrong but contains a SOAPFault without the envelope.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HTTP/1.1 500 Internal Server Error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Content-Type: application/xml; charset=UTF-8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Host: 127.0.0.1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SOAPAction: urn:getQuote&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Date: Wed, 12 Mar 2008 13:20:32 GMT&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Server: Synapse-HttpComponents-NIO&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Transfer-Encoding: chunked&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;14c&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;soapenv:Fault xmlns:soapenv=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2003/05/soap-envelope&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;soapenv:Code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;soapenv:Value xmlns:sf12=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2003/05/soap-envelope&quot;&amp;gt;sf12:Receiver&amp;lt;/soapenv:Value&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;/soapenv:Code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;soapenv:Reason&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;soapenv:Text&amp;gt;Exception occurred when transforming the request/response&amp;lt;/soapenv:Text&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;/soapenv:Reason&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
0&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I think the better way of handling this when it comes to POX is by sending the error details enclosed inside an unqualified element named exception with a HTTP 500 error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What would be the fault in REST? should be the same as POX isn&apos;t it? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577948" author="ruwan" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 17:44:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in the SVN head, for both REST and POX cases the fault will be sent as a POX fault which will be the error string wrapped within a &amp;lt;Exception&amp;gt; element. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12596002" author="evanthika" created="Mon, 12 May 2008 08:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The exception is given as a POX wrapped in the &amp;lt;Exception&amp;gt; tag. Tested on 1.2_QA_B1. The issue will be closed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
